vAlign=3D"top">=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal>The Drushocka evolved on a=
 world very prone to intense lightning storms, probably resulting=
 in their desire to control energy as best they can.<SPAN style=3D=
"mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Physically they rather resemble=
 greenish moss-covered boulders. They move through the oscillatio=
n of these moss fibers along their bodies.</P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNo=
rmal><O:P></O:P></P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal>Suffice to say, they=20=
move very slow. However, they make up for this in physical toughn=
ess. Since they are predominantly composed of silicate based mate=
rials, they are literally as tough as rock.</P>=0A<P class=3DMsoN=
ormal><O:P></O:P></P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal>It is believed that=20=
the Drushocka follow a dictatorial feudal system, with each lesse=
r 'caste' swearing allegiance to a lord above it, and those lords=
 swearing allegiance to a ruler who is chosen by the former ruler=
 before he dies.<SPAN style=3D"mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>T=
he Drushocka are best characterized as inflexible and straightfow=
ard. They see a goal, they move towards it and they attain it. </=
P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal><O:P></O:P></P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal>=
The Drushocka are the mortal enemies of the Eee.<SPAN style=3D"ms=
o-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The Drushocka employ&nbsp;Ion / EM=
P&nbsp;devices as their weapons of choice.<SPAN style=3D"mso-spac=
erun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>Needless to say, they have an extremely a=
dverse affect on the Eee, given that the Eee are composed primari=
ly of energy. The Eee firmly believe that the Drushocka ships are=
 trying to eat them.</P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal>Their prefered we=
apons are Gravity/Area/Ion.</P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE>=0A<P cl=
